This directory contains an example CMB+H0 parameter estimation run.

CHECKING EVERYTHING IS SET UP
=============================

Run:

python ../sampler/test/run_pipeline.py wmap.ini output.fits

If you get any error messages then things are not set up properly.


RUNNING SAMPLING
================

Run the command:

python ../sampler/pymc_sampler/sampler.py wmap.ini



MODEL
=====

These modules are run in this default analysis:

camb_cmb      -  Calculate CMB C_ell
hst           -  Use the Riess et al measurement H_0 = 72 +/- 2
wmap          -  Use the WMAP likelihood function on the CMB C_ell

The parameters used are specified in values.ini

OUTPUT
======

Your output to terminal should look something like this:

Running on one core
Running pipeline:  COSMOPAR/OMEGA_M=2.694775e-01  COSMOPAR/OMEGA_B=4.308746e-02  COSMOPAR/N_S=9.610334e-01  COSMOPAR/A_S=2.104695e-09  COSMOPAR/H0=7.101067e-01  COSMOPAR/OPT_TAU=7.777089e-02
 Initializing WMAP likelihood, version v4.1
Pipeline ran okay.
Got like  -4670.55571318
Running pipeline:  COSMOPAR/OMEGA_M=2.663785e-01  COSMOPAR/OMEGA_B=4.542426e-02  COSMOPAR/N_S=9.485880e-01  COSMOPAR/A_S=2.113925e-09  COSMOPAR/H0=7.131000e-01  COSMOPAR/OPT_TAU=7.983618e-02

... etc ...

